New Records: The Toronto Blue Jays sold 727,819 Loonie Dogs in total, breaking the all-time season record. The most Loonie Dogs sold at a game this year was 71,391 on Aug. 6 against Baltimore Orioles.
Key Match Events: The Red Sox won Tuesday's game 6-5.
Pre-Game Insights: Fans needed to eat 15,377 Loonie Dogs to break the all-time season record, and 21,512 to cross the 700,000 dollar dog threshold.
Post-Match Reflections: The Toronto Blue Jays set a new record for Loonie Dogs sold in a season.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The most ever consumed in one game was 76,627 on Aug. 28, 2023 against the Washington Nationals.
Others: Tuesday was the last 'Loonie Dog' night of the year, with hot dogs on sale for $1 every time the team plays a Tuesday game at Rogers Centre.
Milestones or significant achievements: The Toronto Blue Jays broke the all-time season record for Loonie Dogs sold.
